# Progression_Design

## 1. Applies when
There are levels, skill trees, talents, equipment growth, character building, or
meta progression.

## 2. This document owns
Growth curves; levels; skills; talents; unlocks; experience; equipment growth;
long-term goals.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Base combat numbers (Gameplay_Systems); currency/economy (Resource); run-internal
random pools (Run_Structure in roguelites).

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Document role · 2. Growth curve · 3. Levels & XP · 4. Skills / talents ·
5. Unlocks · 6. Equipment growth · 7. Long-term goals · 8. TODO

## 5. Common boundaries
- Progression vs Economy — growth curve vs currency/prices.
- Progression vs Gameplay — unlock effects reference base numbers, don't redefine.
- Progression vs Meta (roguelite) — persistent growth vs single-run rules.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Unlock effects reference Gameplay numbers, not duplicate them.
- Meta unlocks not mixed into single-run rules.
